Vintage style illustration of two identical antique wooden filing cabinets facing each other, connected by streams of small colorful paper cards flowing between them like a river. The cards carry tiny symbolic icons representing different tools, gears, and geometric shapes. The scene is set on a warm sepia-toned desk surface with an old brass compass and worn leather journal nearby. Soft amber lighting creates a nostalgic atmosphere reminiscent of 1940s technical illustrations. The filing cabinet drawers are partially open, revealing neatly organized index cards. Delicate dotted lines trace the path of information transfer between the two cabinets, suggesting a methodical duplication process. Muted earth tones with pops of dusty orange and teal accent the flowing cards.
